    "text": "Grogginess despite a solid 7.7 h logged usually points at timing and consistency rather than quantity, so start there. With manual logging I can't see when you slept, how regular it is, or any staging, so I'm coaching the levers that reliably work: pick a fixed wake time and hold it every day including weekends, dim screens in the last stretch before bed, cut caffeine after mid-afternoon, and keep alcohol away from bedtime since it fragments sleep even when duration looks fine. Also note grogginess right at the alarm often fades within the first hour and says little about the night. Concrete next step: log bed and wake times daily for two weeks so we can spot the pattern.",
